Description: Engim, Inc. is a fabless developer of wireless system-on-chip technology.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Analysts forecast that the Wireless LAN market will grow from 8 million users in 2002 to 80 million users by 2007. This explosive rate of WLAN adoption is driving the need for high capacity WLAN infrastructure within the enterprise. Additionally, as enterprise deployments continue to grow, IT Managers need WLAN infrastructure products that offer enhanced functional capabilities to reduce deployment complexity, increase network robustness and reduce operational costs. Today’s WLAN silicon is optimized for client applications and not for high capacity WLAN infrastructure applications. By allowing simultaneous communications on all WLAN channels, Engim’s Multi-Channel WLAN Switching Engine chipset enables a new generation of very high performance, cost-effective access points. These chipsets apply Wideband Spectral Processing to standards-based WLAN infrastructure products for the first time, thereby dramatically increasing bandwidth and data throughput and making a whole new range of features and functionality available to users at low cost.
Industry Groups: Hardware, Manufacturing, Mobile, Science and Engineering

Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: At SuperDuper, we believe in spending – and splurging – where it counts, especially in the makeup category where we experiment constantly. We've spoken to experts at Sephora, execs at luxury and mass-market cosmetics companies, celeb manicurists, bloggers, beauty editors, cosmetic chemists, and YouTube stars and everyone agrees: the basic nail polish formula is pretty much the same across the board, from $.99 Wet ‘n Wild to $50 Christian Louboutin. So it all comes down to color, and there just aren’t that many shades of red in the world (or greige or coral or even sheer pink), so we decided to find the dupes for our favorite pricey colors and share ‘em with you. We hope you have fun using SuperDuper and save a few bucks towards your favorite splurges.
